<section xml:id="section-assignment-week2">
  <title>Week 2 Assignment</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following situations, what kind of function
        might you choose to encode the dependence? Give reasons for
        your answer. (10) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          The fuel consumption of a car in terms of velocity. 
        </li>
        <li>
          Salary in an organization in terms of years served. 
        </li>
        <li>
          Windchill adjustment to temperature in terms of windspeed. 
        </li>
        <li>
          Population of rabbits in a valley in terms of time.
        </li>
        <li>
          Ammount of homework required over term in terms of time. 
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following functions, express the function as
        the composition of two other functions. (8) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          <m>\frac{1}{3 + \sin x}</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>\sqrt[3]{\frac{x}{x^2+1}}</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>\sqrt{\ln x} + \frac{1}{\ln x}</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>\frac{1}{x^2} + \frac{1}{4x^2 + 1}</m>
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For the following pairs of functions <m>f</m> and <m>g</m>,
        calculate <m>f \circ g</m> and <m>g \circ f</m>. Simplify the
        expressions for the composition as much as you can. Then state
        the domains of <m>f \circ  g</m> and <m>g \circ f</m>. (15) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = \ln x</m> and <m>x^2</m>. 
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = \sin x</m> and <m>g(x) = \cos x</m>. 
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = x^3 + 7x + 5</m> and <m>g(x) = x^2 + 1</m>. 
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Invert the following functions on the given domain. (You may
        assume the function is monotonic on the given domain). State
        the domain of the inverse. (12) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = e^{(x-2)^2}</m> on the domain <m>(2,\infty)</m>. 
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = \arctan \left( \frac{1}{x-5} \right) </m> on the
          domain <m>\left( 6, \infty \right)</m>. 
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = \frac{6 + x}{3 - x}</m> on the domain
          <m>(3, \infty)</m>. 
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
  </ol></p>
